headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler had a triple-double with 27 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists and the Miami Heat overcame a slow start to beat the slumping Houston Rockets 101-94 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jimmy Butler has triple-double, leads Heat past Rockets

headlines.description: — Semi Ojeleye had a career-high 24 points and six 3-pointers, and the Boston Celtics rolled to a 120-106 win over the Toronto Raptors on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ojeleye scores career-high 24, Celtics down Raptors 120-106

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 26 points, eight rebounds and eight assists, and the Indiana Pacers snapped a four-game losing streak with a 111-95 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers snap 4-game skid with 111-95 win over Pistons

events.name: Orlando Magic at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry knocked down 10 3-pointers on the way to 40 points and also contributed eight rebounds and five assists, leading the Golden State Warriors past the undermanned Orlando Magic 111-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry goes off again with 10 3s as Warriors hold off Magic

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 30 points and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Philadelphia 76ers 118-114 on Thursday night.
